element.name: Kyle Cache 1 by Kyle, Traditional Cache (3/3.5)
element.description: The location of this my first Cache is in Co.Wicklow Ireland. You can access the Cache from any side (ie 360degree range). It is on a small mountain that has a road all the way around it so this means that it is up to you to decided which side is best to attack the challenge. It is an easy Cache and I have given in a 1.5 for both Terrain and general difficulty. It is a easy quick cache and you can drive within .5 of a k of it.
element.long-description:
The Cache is in some loose rocks so mind you don't twist your ankles. You will have to lift a few rocks to see the cache and please do put them back.
The cache is in a Lunch box with a blue lid.
I am not going to reveal the contents, you will have to geocache to find out what is in it.
element.encoded-hints: NO HINTS SORRY IT IS TO EASY AS IT IS

ul.li:
2009-11-08T20:00:00Z : Found it by Moses O'Toole
Glorious day up the hills. Found the cache easily enough, but contents very damp. Took nothing (other than the mouldy Milky Way bar, for disposal in nearest bin!).

2009-10-10T19:00:00Z : Found it by didi2206
Bit damp.. gave it a quick tidy.. took a snail, left a horse hole punch toy. TFTC

2009-08-21T19:00:00Z : Found it by kazidrat
Lovely walk, cache found quickly, but the logbook is wet... TFTC...[:D]

2009-08-16T19:00:00Z : Found it by redflame1
Great climb and super 360 view. Cache is quite damp as others have noted. TFTC TNLN SL.

2009-07-27T19:00:00Z : Found it by Elvistones
Thanks for this beautiful view :)
